Class TimeShifterUpdate

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.flexiblepower.ral.messages.ResourceMessage

        • org.flexiblepower.efi.timeshifter.TimeShifterUpdate

  • public class TimeShifterUpdate
extends ControlSpaceUpdate
    If a new program is scheduled by time shifter appliance the resource manager sends a time shifter control space update towards the energy app.

                 java.util.Date timestamp,
                 java.util.Date validFrom,
                 java.util.Date endBefore,
                 java.util.List<SequentialProfile> timeshifterProfiles)
        Parameters:
        resourceId - The resource identifier
        timestamp - The moment when this constructor is called
        validFrom - This timestamp indicates from which moment on this update is valid.
        endBefore - The moment in time where every sequential profile in the timeShifterProfiles list must be finished.
        timeshifterProfiles - A list of SequentialProfiles representing one or more energy profiles, in a CommodityForecast object, that can be allocated sequentially. The forecast profile is used because there can be an uncertainty in the declared profiles. (e.g. the program a tumble dryer controlled by a sensor does not have a fixed duration and therefore some uncertainty)
